      "commit_title": "[STF] Fix stream_ctx under CUDA graph capture (#8674)",
      "commit_message": "* [stf] Fix stream_ctx under CUDA graph capture\n\nWhen an STF `stream_ctx` is constructed from a user stream that is already\ncapturing (e.g. opened by `cudaStreamBeginCapture(..., Relaxed)` or\n`wp.ScopedCapture`), two problems prevented task submission from completing\nthe capture cleanly:\n\n1. In `task::acquire`, the context's `start_events` were only merged as\n   prerequisites when the task had *zero* dependencies. A task with only\n   `write()`-mode dependencies has no *input* predecessor and therefore was\n   never linked to the context's start event. The first pool stream picked\n   for such a task was then synchronized via `cudaStreamWaitEvent` against\n   an event that was never recorded inside the capture, producing\n   `cudaErrorStreamCaptureIsolation` at submission or finalize time.\n\n   Fix: compute a `has_input_dep` flag in the existing dependency loop (true\n   for `read` / `rw` / `reduce` / `relaxed` accesses, including after mode\n   merging). If the task has no input dependency and the context has start\n   events, merge them as prerequisites. This makes every task's first pool\n   stream fork from the user stream inside the capture, so its subsequent\n   work is correctly captured.\n\n2. Passing a user-supplied `async_resources_handle` together with a\n   capturing user stream is still unsafe: the handle's pool very likely\n   carries streams with residual uncaptured work from prior contexts, and\n   CUDA will reject folding them into the ongoing capture. Reject this\n   configuration early with a clear `EXPECT` message.\n\nTo implement the check cleanly without losing move semantics on the handle,\n`backend_ctx_untyped::impl` now records `user_provided_handle =\nbool(async_resources)` in its member initializer list *before* the handle is\nmoved in. `stream_ctx(cudaStream_t, async_resources_handle)` then inspects\n`state().user_provided_handle` in its body and, if set, asserts that\n`user_stream` is not currently capturing.\n\nAdds `cudax/test/stf/local_stf/legacy_to_stf_in_capture.cu`, which runs a\ndiamond-DAG workload twice under an explicit `cudaStreamBeginCapture` in\nrelaxed mode -- once with hand-wired event-based dependencies, once through\n`stream_ctx` + tokens -- compares the instantiated graphs, validates the\nhost-side result, and also checks that constructing\n`stream_ctx(capture_stream, handle)` during an active capture triggers the\nnew assertion.\n\nMade-with: Cursor\n\n* [stf] Fix cudaGraphNodeGetDependencies arity for pre-CTK 13\n\nThe ``cudaGraphNodeGetDependencies`` runtime API grew an ``edgeData``\nparameter in CTK 13. Guard both call sites with ``_CCCL_CTK_AT_LEAST(13, 0)``\nto match the pattern already used in ``graph_task.cuh`` so the test builds\non the older toolkits still exercised in CI.\n\nMade-with: Cursor\n\n* [STF] Reject non-canonical access_mode merge results\n\nMerging duplicate logical-data dependencies uses bitwise OR on the\nunderlying unsigned. Some combinations (e.g. read|reduce) yield values\nthat are not handled by the MSI protocol. Require the merged result to be\none of none, read, write, rw, reduce, or reduce_no_init and document this\nwith access_mode_merge_result_is_well_formed.\n\nMade-with: Cursor\n\n* [STF] Inline access_mode merge validation in operator|\n\nRemove access_mode_merge_result_is_well_formed; validate the merged enum\nwith a switch inside operator|.\n\nMade-with: Cursor\n\n* Fix CI: clang-format constants.cuh; CTK13 graph dep query in capture test\n\n- Apply clang-format to access_mode operator| (pre-commit.ci).\n- legacy_to_stf_in_capture: pass cudaGraphEdgeData storage to\n  cudaGraphNodeGetDependencies on CTK 13+; nullptr edgeData with non-default\n  edge annotations yields cudaErrorLossyQuery and broke cudax STF tests.\n\nMade-with: Cursor\n\n* STF: skip cuStreamGetId while stream is in graph capture\n\ncuStreamGetId is not permitted on a stream that is capturing (CUDA_ERROR_\nSTREAM_CAPTURE_UNSUPPORTED). set_user_stream wraps the user stream in\ndecorated_stream, which called get_stream_id immediately.\n\nReturn k_no_stream_id when cudaStreamIsCapturing reports a non-none status;\nasync_resources already treats unknown ids as requiring explicit syncs.\n\nMade-with: Cursor\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Andrei Alexandrescu <andrei@erdani.com>"
    },
